# Cursor Rules for Incognito Fingerprint Project

## Project Overview
This is an advanced anti-fingerprinting browser extension and userscript project that provides comprehensive protection against browser fingerprinting techniques.

## Key Files
- `manifest.json` - Chrome extension manifest (Manifest V3)
- `shared-utils.js` - Core anti-fingerprinting utilities
- `script-loader.js` - Content script loader for incognito mode
- `popup.js` - Extension popup UI logic
- `ultimate-anti-fingerprint.user.js` - Comprehensive userscript
- `background.js` - Extension background service worker

## Development Guidelines
1. Always update version numbers in manifest.json, package.json, and userscript metadata
2. Test protection on fingerprinting test sites (Am I Unique, etc.)
3. Ensure compatibility with incognito mode
4. Maintain consistent Chrome/Windows profile spoofing
5. Use subtle randomization to avoid detection

## MCP Server Configuration
The project uses MCP servers for enhanced development capabilities.

